{{SetCustomerMetadataAttribute(
    idn="project_attributes_catering_menu",
    field="multiple_fields",
    value={ "title": "3-07. Catering Menu [A]", "description": """This attribute stores the catering menu as plain text, which is then used by the system for handling
orders and recommendations.

To ensure the menu is properly formatted, it is recommended to include:

- Dish name
- Description (ingredients, preparation style, special features)
- Category (e.g., \"appetizers\", \"main courses\", \"desserts\", \"beverages\")
- Price

Example:

```txt
- **Margherita Pizza**
Description: Classic Italian pizza with tomato sauce, fresh mozzarella, and basil.
Category: Main Course.
Price: $12.99.
- **New York Cheesecake**
Description: A creamy, rich cheesecake with a crunchy base.
Category: Desserts.
Price: $7.50.
```

If the menu includes this information, the system can better understand customer requests and find
the right dishes during conversations.""", "group": "3. Knowledge Base", "value_type": "string", "is_hidden": False }
)}}

